ENGINEERING NOTICE

The fire-resistance-rated wall assemblies, details, calculations, and code
analyses contained in this repository are published for educational and
reference purposes. They represent a generalized engineering approach to
demonstrating compliance with IBC Section 703.2.2(4) — Engineering Analysis
based on a comparison of building element, component, or assembly designs
having fire-resistance ratings as determined by the test procedures set forth
in ASTM E119 or UL 263.

Use of these details on a real project requires:

  1. Site-specific review by a Professional Engineer licensed in the
     jurisdiction of the project.
  2. Acceptance by the Authority Having Jurisdiction (AHJ) under IBC
     Section 104.11 — Alternative Materials, Design and Methods of
     Construction and Equipment.
  3. Verification that proprietary products specified (intumescent coatings,
     gypsum board, insulation, sealants) match the listings referenced and
     are installed per the manufacturer's listed thickness, primer, topcoat,
     and substrate preparation requirements.

Oasis Engineering, LLC offers PE stamping and project-specific engineering
analysis based on these assemblies. Contact: oasisengineering.com

